Former S.Korean intelligence official faces for leaking wiretap.
Gong had headed a special wiretapping team from the National Intelligence Service, the main spy agency.
South Korean prosecutors said Thurday they have secured an arrest warrant for a former intelligence official accused of leaking a taped conversation detailing a slush fund payment by the Samsung Group.
Gong Un-Yong, 58, is accused of handing over the taped conversation to a Korean-American businessman who was arrested last week.
Gong has been hospitalized since he attempted to commit suicide nine days ago.
